{"id":28476,"title":"New drugs and indications in 2013: little real progress but regulatory authorities take some positive steps.","abstract":"2013 saw few therapeutic innovations that really benefitted patients; once again, marketing authorisations were too often granted despite inadequate clinical data. The French health authorities implemented a few measures designed to protect patients from dangerous drugs, including market withdrawals, restrictions on use, and delisting.","date":"2014-05-23","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24860905","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.800352,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.758052,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.734333,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Regulation","weight":0.669488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation"},{"name":"Marketing","weight":0.465942,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marketing"},{"name":"Drug development","weight":0.377973,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_development"},{"name":"Market","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Market"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.289795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data"},{"name":"Narcotic","weight":0.26893,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narcotic"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.112661,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Regulatory agency","weight":0.0554043,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulatory_agency"},{"name":"France","weight":0.0243874,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France"},{"name":"Reality","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reality"}]}
